How to install (and run) Cytoscape on Linux

1. Run `sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-11-jdk wget xvfb` in the terminal.
2. Run `wget https://github.com/cytoscape/cytoscape/releases/download/3.8.0/cytoscape-unix-3.8.0.tar.gz` in the terminal.
3. Run `tar xf cytoscape-unix-3.8.0.tar.gz` in the terminal.
4. Add the decompressed cytoscape-unix-3.8.0 directory path to the $PATH environmental variable.

How to install Cytoscape on Mac

1. Run `wget https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk11-binaries/releases/download/jdk-11.0.7%2B10/OpenJDK11U-jdk_x64_mac_hotspot_11.0.7_10.pkg` in the terminal.
2. Run `open OpenJDK11U-jdk_x64_mac_hotspot_11.0.7_10.pkg` in the terminal.
3. Run `wget https://github.com/cytoscape/cytoscape/releases/download/3.8.0/cytoscape-unix-3.8.0.tar.gz` in the terminal.
4. Run `tar xf cytoscape-unix-3.8.0.tar.gz` in the terminal.
5. Add the decompressed cytoscape-unix-3.8.0 directory path to the $PATH environmental variable.

How to install Cytoscape on Windows

1. Download https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk11-binaries/releases/download/jdk-11.0.7%2B10.2/OpenJDK11U-jdk_x64_windows_hotspot_11.0.7_10.msi
2. Install OpenJDK11U-jdk_x64_windows_hotspot_11.0.7_10.msi
3. Download https://github.com/cytoscape/cytoscape/releases/download/3.8.0/cytoscape-windows-3.8.0.zip
4. Unzip cytoscape-windows-3.8.0.zip
5. Add the decompressed cytoscape-windows-3.8.0 folder path to PATH environmental variable.